        <updateDate>2019-02-07T20:48:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Rural Broadband Connectivity Act of 2018 </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax credit for a portion of the cost of a broadband project designed to expand the number of individuals with broadband service in a qualified rural census tract. A &quot;qualified rural census tract&quot; must be designated by the Department of the Treasury as: (1) being rural, and (2) having less than 50% of residents with access to broadband service. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
